# VPS Development Configuration
# When using `just dev-web-vps`, the web-app connects to VPS API via SSH tunnel
#
# Requirements:
#   - 1Password with SSH agent enabled (Developer settings â†’ SSH Agent)
#   - SSH key for VPS stored in 1Password
#   - VPS API must be running and accessible
#
# VPS Connection Settings (REQUIRED for dev-web-vps):
VPS_HOST=your-vps-hostname-or-ip
VPS_USER=your-ssh-username
VPS_API_PORT=8000

# 1Password SSH Agent Socket (REQUIRED for dev-web-vps on macOS):
# Set this to your 1Password SSH agent socket path
# Default macOS path (replace with your actual path):
OP_SSH_SOCKET=~/Library/Group Containers/2BUA8C4S2C.com.1password/t/agent.sock

# The docker-compose.vps-dev.yml configuration:
#   - Uses 1Password SSH agent for secure key management
#   - Creates SSH tunnel service: localhost:${VPS_API_PORT} -> VPS:${VPS_API_PORT}
#   - Runs web-app with hot reload (pnpm dev)
#   - Configures web-app with: NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://ssh-tunnel:8000
#   - No local database, cache, or other services needed (uses VPS)
#
# Commands:
#   - just dev-web-vps        # Start VPS development environment
#   - just dev-web-vps-down   # Stop VPS development environment
#
# Testing:
#   - Web app: http://localhost:3000
#   - VPS API (via tunnel): http://localhost:${VPS_API_PORT}/ping
#
# Security Features:
#   - SSH host key verification enabled (prevents MITM attacks)
#   - Ports bound to localhost only (not accessible from network)
#   - No hardcoded credentials or IP addresses in git
#   - 1Password manages SSH keys securely
